I tried to get this on 2 nights ago, but the site went down.<br><br>
      from: JANE'S DEFENSE WEEKLY - July 2, 1997, pg.13<br><br>
                   VIETNAM MINE KILLS SIX<br><br>
An anti-tank mine left over from the Vietnam War has killed 6 people after exploding under a truck in Tay Ninh province near Cambodia.  The driver, 3 farmers and 2 soldiers were killed in the explosion.
